headline: Lambda and ECL Bring the First Hydrogen-Powered NVIDIA GB300 NVL72 Systems Online
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, September 23, 2025--Lambda, the Superintelligence Cloud, today announced the deployment of the industry’s first hydrogen-powered, production-grade NVIDIA GB300 NVL72 systems at ECL’s Mountain View campus (MV1), a zero-water and zero-emissions off-grid modular data center that operates entirely on hydrogen fuel cells for AI inference and foundational model training with unprecedented efficiency.

headline: What Super Micro Computer (SMCI)'s New AI Server Launches and Liquid Cooling Push Mean for Shareholders
summary: Earlier this month, Super Micro Computer introduced a significant line-up of new AI-optimized servers and systems at its INNOVATE! event in Madrid, featuring NVIDIA's HGX B300, GB300 NVL72, Jetson Orin NX, and Intel Xeon 6 SoC processors, with liquid cooling technology for data center efficiency. This rollout underscores Supermicro's increased global manufacturing reach and its collaborative approach with key technology partners to address growing data center and AI infrastructure needs,...
